Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Thinly slice @mini cucumber{1} on a
diagonal. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; mince
whites. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}.

== Sweet Potato Wedges ==

Toss sweet potatoes on a foil-lined #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, half
the soy sauce (you'll use the rest in Step 4), and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Firecracker Sauce & Ponzu Cucumbers ==

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon},
@honey{2%teaspoon}, half the ponzu, and @sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Set sauce aside.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters}(remaining), @sugar{1/4%teaspoon},
and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Pork Patties ==

In a second large bowl, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup},
scallion whites, ginger, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}(remaining), @salt, and pepper.

Form into 8 1-inch meatballs (16 meatballs for 4).

> TIP: Rub hands with a little oil first to prevent sticking.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add meatballs; gently
press down with a #spatula{} to make ½-inch-thick patties. (TIP: Depending on the size
of your pan, you may need to cook in batches.) Cook until browned and cooked through,
~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Carefully add patties to bowl with sauce; toss to coat.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

== Assembly ==

Halve @demi-baguettes{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through.
Toast in a #toaster{} or under the broiler until golden.

Divide toasted baguettes and sweet potato wedges between plates. Fill baguettes
with patties; top with as much sauce and cucumber as you like. Sprinkle with
scallion greens and close sandwiches. Serve with any remaining cucumber on the side
and any remaining sauce for dipping.